cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep-learning-based approach for one-class classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces two loss functions and a parallel CNN architecture, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The proposed method is also evaluated on anomaly detection and mobile authentication datasets, which are related to computer security (cs.CR) and multimedia (cs.MM), respectively, making them possible sub-categories.
